<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-657] AbstractDatabaseManager doesn&apos;t close connection on writeInternal error</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-657</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using the JDBCAppender: if the AbstractDatabaseManager.writeInternal() method fails (e.g. value to large for column size, or any other database error) the database connection is not closed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve attached a proposed patch to fix this - please take a look and see if it makes sense to handle write failures this way.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
